{"_id":"9x8XQ0VcqBk0je06","name":"Soul Survivor","type":"class","img":"systems/vastgrimm/assets/images/tokens/classes/soul-survivor.png","data":{"abilities":"<p>Scrawny 3d6-2 Strength. Cockroach, all Presence and Toughness tests have their DR reduced by 2. Roll d6 on the weapon table and d2 on the armor table.</p>","armorTableDie":"1d2","description":"Wherever you go, a dark cloud looms over your filthy, bug-infested head. You drag it along with you like a dead dog on a leash, darkening those you keep company with. But what can be done? The shadows are where you thrive. When all is bleak, you will profit or at least be the last to die.","favorDie":"1d2","startingAgility":"3d6","startingCredits":"1d6*10","startingHitPoints":"1d6","startingItems":"vastgrimm.class-soul-survivor,Cockroach","startingPresence":"3d6","startingRolls":"vastgrimm.rolls-soul-survivor,Traumatic Loneliness,1\nvastgrimm.rolls-soul-survivor,Soul Survivor Skillz,1\nvastgrimm.character-creation,Starting Equipment - 1,1\nvastgrimm.character-creation,Starting Equipment - 2,1\nvastgrimm.character-creation,Starting Equipment - 3,1","startingStrength":"3d6-2","startingToughness":"3d6","weaponTableDie":"1d6"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"2oqn6Iy7EPH48MYr":3},"flags":{}}
{"name":"Get Anywhere/Anything","type":"skill","img":"systems/vastgrimm/assets/images/tokens/classes/soul-survivor.png","data":{"description":"<p>You&rsquo;ve managed to find your way in and out of everywhere you&rsquo;ve been, often by picking locks and pockets. You can do both with an Agility DR8. You have an antique set of lockpicks and a decrypted keycard.</p>","rollFormula":"","rollLabel":""},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"2oqn6Iy7EPH48MYr":3},"flags":{},"_id":"IrgoXUX3obus3N6d"}
{"name":"Inevitable Escape","type":"skill","img":"systems/vastgrimm/assets/images/tokens/classes/soul-survivor.png","data":{"description":"<p>You, better than anyone else, know how to find places out of harm&rsquo;s way. When hiding during combat, it takes a Presence DR14 test to notice you.</p>","rollFormula":"","rollLabel":""},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"2oqn6Iy7EPH48MYr":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.xuRoiU1qRtyVeOCK"}},"_id":"Mj7HS1mrmlGg3RSL"}
{"name":"Shrunken Stomach","type":"skill","img":"systems/vastgrimm/assets/images/tokens/classes/soul-survivor.png","data":{"description":"<p>Having spent much of your life with little or no food, your stomach has adjusted to being malnourished. Without food, you can restore d4 HP for three days. On the seventh day, you begin&nbsp;</p>","rollFormula":"","rollLabel":""},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"2oqn6Iy7EPH48MYr":3},"flags":{},"_id":"Sfh3ik6HZ0QqW58s"}
{"name":"Low Expectations","type":"skill","img":"systems/vastgrimm/assets/images/tokens/classes/soul-survivor.png","data":{"description":"<p>No one expects much of you. Most assume you will slink back into a corner if threatened. Your first attack is always a surprise with a DR10. Succeed by 5 or more and double your damage.</p>","rollFormula":"","rollLabel":""},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"2oqn6Iy7EPH48MYr":3},"flags":{},"_id":"a7gbv3joVTDt90ji"}
{"name":"Energy Vampire","type":"skill","img":"systems/vastgrimm/assets/images/tokens/classes/soul-survivor.png","data":{"description":"<p>You begin with one trait: ENERGY VAMPIRE Pain and misery fuels you as you feed on the emotional energy of others. When a member of YOUR LEGION is killed, gain 1 additional Favor. If more than half of YOUR LEGION was there to witness it, and it was exceptionally brutal, gain 2.</p>","rollFormula":"","rollLabel":""},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"2oqn6Iy7EPH48MYr":3},"flags":{},"_id":"aHFV7hszBYZ3RPxM"}
{"name":"Last to Die","type":"skill","img":"systems/vastgrimm/assets/images/tokens/classes/soul-survivor.png","data":{"description":"<p>You are weak and puny. Everyone looks at you and sees zer0 threat and even chuckles at the idea of your mere existence. When fighting alongside YOUR LEGION, you will always be the last to be attacked, if you&rsquo;re even worth their time.</p>","rollFormula":"","rollLabel":""},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"2oqn6Iy7EPH48MYr":3},"flags":{},"_id":"odUBZmjnflneklCn"}
